dataIdInfo.idAbs: Ireland feature class has been created from original Ireland 1:50K Discovery Series shapefile layer. ArcInfo was used to clean and edit geometry errors along the coastline. This cleaned layer was saved as a shapefile and loaded as a personal geodatabase into ArcSDE. This is the most accurate layer outlining the Irish coastline and is the geodatabase Feature Class layer to use for mapping inshore areas such as bays and estuaries and out to the 50m contour. This dataset has been purchased from the Ordnance Survey of Ireland (ie. OSi) and is only usable under their licence terms. Please contact Data Management if you are using this dataset in publication quality maps.
